HEADWORD: Pleurapophysis
<hw>Pleu`ra*poph"y*sis</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Pleurapophyses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu>
<ety>[NL. See <er>Pleura</er>, and <er>Apophysis</er>.]</ety>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <def>One of the ventral processes of a vertebra, or
the dorsal element in each half of a hemal arch, forming, or
corresponding to, a vertebral rib.</def> --
<wordforms><wf>Pleu*rap`o*phys"i*al</wf> <pr>(#)</pr>,
<pos>a.</pos></wordforms> <rj><au>Owen.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
